
/*
 * // This Hyperlambda code checks if a file exists at a path specified by a string replacement operation. 
 * // If the file exists, it sets the value of a node named [.filename] to the result of the string replacement.
 * // 1. [if] - Initiates a conditional check.
 * // 2. [io.file.exists] - Checks if a file exists at the path resulting from the string replacement.
 * // 3. [strings.replace] - Performs a string replacement operation to determine the file path.
 * // 4. [.lambda] - Executes the following code block if the condition is true.
 * // 5. [set-value] - Sets the value of [.filename] to the result of the string replacement.
 * // 6. [get-value] - Retrieves the result of the string replacement to set as the value of [.filename].
 */
if
   io.file.exists:x:@strings.replace
   .lambda
      set-value:x:@.filename
         get-value:x:@strings.replace
